article.headline: Incarnate Word earns 79-75 win against Houston Christian
article.description: — Sky Wicks' 17 points helped Incarnate Word defeat Houston Christian 79-75 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Incarnate Word earns 79-75 win against Houston Christian
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Sky Wicks' 17 points helped Incarnate Word defeat Houston Christian 79-75 on Saturday night. Wicks added 11 rebounds and six assists for the Cardinals (6-13, 1-5 Southland Conference). Alex Anderson scored 16 points while going 6 of 12 and 4 of 5 from the free-throw line. Josiah Hammons shot 4 for 14, including 4 for 13 from beyond the arc to finish with 13 points. The win snapped a five-game skid for the Cardinals. Jay Alvarez finished with 21 points, four assists and two steals for the Huskies (5-13, 3-4). Houston Christian also got 16 points and eight rebounds from Bonke Maring. In addition, Marcus Greene had 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
